  "text": "Hyperlipidemia is a common and serious problem among adult renal and bone marrow stem cell transplantation recipients and patients with malignancies, and it has been demonstrated that the condition contributes to an increase in the risk of cardiovascular diseases and elevated morbidity and mortality within these populations [CITATION_1] . Previous research has demonstrated an association between plasma/serum lipoproteins and different types of cancers, such as breast, prostate and gynecological cancer and acute lymphoblastic leukemia [CITATION_2] . The main question is whether dyslipidemia predisposes one to cancer or whether it is an effect of the malignancy.",
